{"questionId":"2738101","questionHtml":"<p>Consider the equation <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><msup><mi>z</mi><mn>2</mn></msup><mo>=</mo><mn>2</mn><msup><mi>z</mi><mo>*</mo></msup></math>, where <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>z</mi><mo>∈</mo><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">ℂ</mi></math>, <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>z</mi><mo>≠</mo><mn>0</mn></math>.</p>\n<p>By expressing <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>z</mi></math> in the form <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>a</mi><mo>+</mo><mi>b</mi><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">i</mi></math>, find the roots of the equation.</p>","markschemeHtml":"<p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><msup><mrow><mo>(</mo><mi>a</mi><mo>+</mo><mi>b</mi><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">i</mi><mo>)</mo></mrow><mn>2</mn></msup><mo>=</mo><mn>2</mn><mo>(</mo><mi>a</mi><mo>-</mo><mi>b</mi><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">i</mi><mo>)</mo></math>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;<em><strong> A1</strong></em></p>\n<p>attempts to expand and equate real and imaginary parts:&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;<em><strong> M1</strong></em></p>\n<p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><msup><mi>a</mi><mn>2</mn></msup><mo>-</mo><msup><mi>b</mi><mn>2</mn></msup><mo>=</mo><mn>2</mn><mi>a</mi><mi>b</mi><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">i</mi><mo>=</mo><mn>2</mn><mi>a</mi><mo>-</mo><mn>2</mn><mi>b</mi><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">i</mi></math></p>\n<p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><msup><mi>a</mi><mn>2</mn></msup><mo>-</mo><msup><mi>b</mi><mn>2</mn></msup><mo>=</mo><mn>2</mn><mi>a</mi></math> and <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>2</mn><mi>a</mi><mi>b</mi><mo>=</mo><mo>-</mo><mn>2</mn><mi>b</mi></math></p>\n<p>attempts to find the value of <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>a</mi></math> or <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>b</mi></math>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;<em><strong> M1</strong></em></p>\n<p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>2</mn><mi>b</mi><mo>(</mo><mi>a</mi><mo>+</mo><mn>1</mn><mo>)</mo><mo>=</mo><mn>0</mn></math></p>\n<p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>b</mi><mo>=</mo><mn>0</mn><mo>⇒</mo><msup><mi>a</mi><mn>2</mn></msup><mo>=</mo><mn>2</mn><mi>a</mi><mo>⇒</mo><mi>a</mi><mo>=</mo><mn>2</mn></math> (real root)&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;<em><strong> A1</strong></em></p>\n<p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>a</mi><mo>=</mo><mo>-</mo><mn>1</mn><mo>⇒</mo><mn>1</mn><mo>-</mo><msup><mi>b</mi><mn>2</mn></msup><mo>=</mo><mo>-</mo><mn>2</mn><mo>⇒</mo><mi>b</mi><mo>=</mo><mo>±</mo><msqrt><mn>3</mn></msqrt></math> (complex roots <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mo>-</mo><mn>1</mn><mo>±</mo><msqrt><mn>3</mn></msqrt><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">i</mi></math>)&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;<em><strong> A1</strong></em></p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p><em><strong>[5 marks]</strong></em></p>","meta":{"questionId":"2738101","referenceCode":"23M.1.AHL.TZ2.11d","subjectId":"50-dp-mathematics-analysis-and-approaches","title":"Consider the equation z2=2z*, where z∈ℂ, z≠0. By expressing z in the form a+bi, find the roots of the equation.","paper":"1","level":"HL","questionNumber":"d","marksAvailable":"[Maximum mark: 5]","breadcrumbLabels":["Topic 1—Number and algebra","Topic 2—Functions","Topic 3— Geometry and trigonometry","Topic 3— Geometry and trigonometry","SL 3.5—Unit circle definitions of sin, cos, tan. Exact trig ratios, ambiguous case of sine rule","Topic 3— Geometry and trigonometry","AHL 3.9—Reciprocal trig ratios and their pythagorean identities. Inverse circular functions","Topic 2—Functions","SL 2.10—Solving equations graphically and analytically","Topic 2—Functions","AHL 2.12—Factor and remainder theorems, sum